	wordHeading={`His Word will not return empty`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not see it right away, and that's okay. Every verse you read with a child is a little seed of God's love planted in their heart — and seeds grow quietly, day by day. God promises that His words always do good work.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My words will not come back empty. They will always do the good thing I send them to do." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I made you, and I love you so much. I know your name, and I know everything about you — when you laugh, when you cry, and even when you're scared in the dark. I am always with you, and I will never leave you."</p><p>"You don't have to be perfect for Me to love you. I loved you first, and I will love you forever. You are My child, and I am so glad you're Mine. When you feel afraid, hold My hand — I am right here."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for kids`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, thank You for making me and for loving me so much. Thank You that You know my name and You are always with me.</p><p>When I feel scared or sad, help me remember that You are right here holding my hand. Help me be brave and kind, and help me know that You love me no matter what.</p><p>Thank You that I am Your child. In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
