		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for children?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read and you can read or hear any chapter together, which is perfect for bedtime, the car, or snuggling up to listen as a family.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about God loving kids?`, answer: `The Bible is full of God's love for children. Jesus said, "Let the little children come to Me" (Matthew 19:14). Zephaniah 3:17 says God sings over you with love, and 1 John 4:19 says He loved us first. The Father's Heart Bible™ shows God as a good, good Father who made your child and loves them no matter what — read it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ good for kids?`, answer: `It reveals God as a loving Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father, so children meet the One who made them and loves them most — not a list of rules. It's written in clear English and is free with audio, so even young kids can listen along. That helps a child grow up knowing the most important truth: God made me, He knows my name, and He loves me no matter what.` },
		{ question: `How can my child start reading the Bible?`, answer: `Start small and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, choose a short Psalm, and listen to the audio while you read together. Try one verse a day — Psalm 139, Psalm 23, or John 3:16 are lovely places to begin. Our verses-by-topic and how-to-pray pages can help you find simple words for whatever your child is feeling.` },
